      <description>&lt;p&gt;Chen is a PhD student in &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.ucl.ac.uk&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;UCL&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/home/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Department of Computer Science&lt;/a&gt;. His research interests cover &lt;a href=&#34;http://cip.cs.ucl.ac.uk/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Inverse Problems&lt;/a&gt;, an area in Mathematics solving for hidden variables given observations &amp;amp; forward models explaining the observations with hidden variables, &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayesian_inference&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Bayesian Inference&lt;/a&gt;, an area in Statistics modelling data with likelihood functions &amp;amp; prior information as well as exploring the posterior distributions by sophisticated approximations, and &lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_learning&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Machine Learning&lt;/a&gt; which connects solid mathematical and statistical analysis to exciting real world problems. His research is fully funded by UCL Computer Science Departmental Studentship at overseas standard.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Besides being a junior researcher, Chen is also a street photographer. He is invited to be one of the first six UCL photographers for &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ucl.ac.uk/news/student-news/get-involved/instagrammer-residence/chen-zhang&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;UCL Instagrammer in Residence&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
